<subSubSection id="AAB96554A663FF8C4889B914B9E7FB60" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E21C36DFA663FF8C4889B914B9E7FB60" blockId="3.[113,737,1083,1790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
Note. Since the 
<typeStatus id="3D18887DA663FF8C4960B914BA44FBA4" box="[327,370,1084,1103]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C49DCB913B99BFBA5" authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1894" box="[507,685,1083,1102]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santarema">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C49DCB913B99BFBA5" box="[507,685,1083,1102]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Helvetia santarema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have not been examined, the synonymy is established based on the good illustrations by 
<bibRefCitation id="86324B2EA663FF8C496EB950B97FFB61" author="PECKHAM &amp; PECKHAM" box="[329,585,1143,1163]" firstAuthor="PECKHAM" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Papers of the Natural History Society of Wisconsin" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" pagination="85 - 156" part="2" refId="ref6708" refString="PECKHAM, G. W. &amp; E. G. PECKHAM. 1894. Spiders of the Marptusa group. Occasional Papers of the Natural History Society of Wisconsin 2: 85 - 156." title="Spiders of the Marptusa group" type="journal article" year="1894">PECKHAM &amp; PECKHAM (1894</bibRefCitation>
, figs 2, 2a-d).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AAB96554A663FF8C4889B9BDB95CFAE9" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E21C36DFA663FF8C4889B9BDB95CFAE9" blockId="3.[113,737,1083,1790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
Diagnosis. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C49B2B9BDB97BFB43" authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1894" box="[405,589,1173,1192]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santarema">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C49B2B9BDB97BFB43" box="[405,589,1173,1192]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Helvetia santarema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C48E2B99CBA70FB2D" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[197,326,1203,1223]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albovittata">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C48E2B99CBBE3FB2D" box="[197,213,1204,1222]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C48C7B99BBA70FB2D" box="[224,326,1203,1222]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">albovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the very long copulatory ducts (
<figureCitation id="7A982A5AA663FF8C485FB9F8BB89FB0F" box="[120,191,1232,1252]" captionStart="Figures 11-14" captionStartId="5.[113,180,1154,1174]" captionTargetBox="[248,1259,194,1141]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[242,1263,181,1150]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 11-14. Epigynum of (11-12) Helvetia santarema: (11) ventral view̡ (12) dorsal view; (13-14) Helvetia albovittata: (13) ventral view̡ (14) dorsal view. Bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3678508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3678508/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by having very closely set copulatory openings, forming an atrium (
