<subSubSection id="AAB96554A663FF8C4889B84FB9A0F929" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E21C36DFA663FF8C4889B84FB9A0F929" blockId="3.[113,737,1083,1790]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
Note. 
<bibRefCitation id="86324B2EA663FF8C48CDB84FBAB0FA91" author="GALIANO" box="[234,390,1382,1402]" firstAuthor="GALIANO" journalOrPublisher="Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" pagination="1 - 8" part="24" refId="ref6456" refString="GALIANO, M. E. 1963 b. Nota sobre aranas del grupo Marpisseae (Araneae, Salticidae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 24: 1 - 8." title="Nota sobre aranas del grupo Marpisseae (Araneae, Salticidae)" type="journal article" year="1963" yearSuffix="b">GALIANO (1963b)</bibRefCitation>
supposedly found the male of this species described by Mello-Leitão as 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C49F6B8ACB9B1FA7C" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1943" box="[465,647,1412,1431]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cotinusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humillima">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C49F6B8ACB9B1FA7C" box="[465,647,1412,1431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Cotinusa humillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, synonymizing these species. This male has a shorter embolus than that expected to be present in this species. The general epigynal conformation of 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C48D1B8F6BA44FA1B" authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1894" box="[246,370,1502,1521]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santarema">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C48D1B8F6BA30FA1B" box="[246,262,1502,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C4934B8F6BA44FA1B" box="[275,370,1502,1520]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">santarema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very close to that of 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C4A7CB8F6B9EDFA1A" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[603,731,1502,1521]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albovittata">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C4A7CB8F6B9EDFA1A" box="[603,731,1502,1521]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">H. albovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with very long copulatory ducts. The male of 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C4A00B8D4B992F9E5" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[551,676,1531,1550]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albovittata">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C4A00B8D4B992F9E5" box="[551,676,1531,1550]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">H. albovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, has a very long embolus, arising very proximally in the palp and making a loop on the retrolateral, distal part of the cymbium, which is itself modified to hold it. Since there seems to be a very strong correlation between the length of the embolus and the length of the copulatory ducts, Galiano’s establishment is considered erroneous and 
<taxonomicName id="25A34D5CA663FF8C4977BB87B931F929" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1943" box="[336,519,1711,1730]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Cotinusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humillima">
<emphasis id="D0D7EACDA663FF8C4977BB87B931F929" box="[336,519,1711,1730]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Cotinusa humillima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is revalidated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
